   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>83 8.6.8.6.6.6.7.5. with chorus.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>As I am fighting for my Lord,</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The devil won't give in;</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Satan with dark authority</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Resists when I begin.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>But as I pray with might</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>That evil would take flight,</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Calling, talking with my Lord,</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>All things will be right.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Chorus</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To call on Him and talk to Him</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Makes all things right;</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To call on Him and talk to Him</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Makes all things right.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Praise to my Lord, whene'er</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>I would the least despair</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To call on Him and talk to Him</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Makes all things right.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Passing through dark, uncertain ways,</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Facing torrent and wind,</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Though bitter hardship be my lot,</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Met with apparent end,</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>There's victory in sight,</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>An Overcomer's might;</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>He's the One I call upon,</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>All things will be right.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>When homefolks are accusing me,</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Loved ones' contact lost,</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>When I am lonely, poor, and weak</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>And by rejection tossed,</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>To Him I bring my need,</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>I'm comforted indeed.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Truly when I come to Him,</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>All things will be right.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Since often I converse with Him,</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>No anxious cares molest;</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Daily I can rejoice and sing,</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Lean on His loving breast.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>I'll rest upon His might</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Until the end's in sight;</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Just to call and talk to Him,</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>All things will be right.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
